no.motif.types

Interface Elements<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the contained objects.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Appendable<T>, Existance<T>, Filterable<T>, HeadAndTail<T>, Iterable<T>, Mappable<T>, Prependable<T>, Reducible<T>, Repeatable<T>, SideEffectable<T>, YieldsJavaCollection<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PreparedIterable

    public interface Elements<T>
extends Mappable<T>, Filterable<T>, Appendable<T>, Prependable<T>, SideEffectable<T>, Repeatable<T>, HeadAndTail<T>, YieldsJavaCollection<T>, Existance<T>, Iterable<T>, Reducible<T>
    This is the main type of Motif's collection API and encompasses all the operations available to manipulate and query the the contained elements, as well as converting back to Java Collection Framework collections.

      • eval

        Elements<T> eval()
        Force-evaluate the current elements, applying all composed functions on each element. This is useful when needing to iterate elements several times, especially if the composed functions are expensive to evaluate and/or not referentially transparent. This is an escape-hatch from the lazy design of Elements.
        Returns:
        same type of elements, with all elements evaluated.
